    <Object Type="Vector.CANalyzer.Panels.Design.StaticTextControl, Vector.CANalyzer.Panels.CommonControls, Version=17.3.40.0, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=null" Name="StaticTextControl2" Children="Controls" ControlName="Static Text">
      <Property Name="Name">StaticTextControl2</Property>
      <Property Name="Size">505, 247</Property>
      <Property Name="Location">19, 157</Property>
      <Property Name="BackColor">HighlightText</Property>
      <Property Name="Text">The signals are used as follows:

Channel 01 is an output that generates a signal depending on the button labelled 'CANoe Start/Stop'.
This signal is used to mimic an active CANoe session.
It also controls the 'traffic light' on the DUT (red or not red).

Channel 02 is an output that generates a signal depending on the button labelled 'DUT Start/Stop'.
This signal is used to show the state (active or idle) of the DUT.
It also controls the 'traffic light' on the DUT (yellow or green).

Channels 03..06 are inputs used to measure the bits of the 4-bit counter of the DUT.
They are used to calculate the counter value that is displayed on the CANoe panel.
Bit0 is also used to calculate the counter frequency.

Channel 07 is an input that is used to detect the signal from the button labelled 'DUT Start/Stop'.
It detects a positive edge of the button signal. The CANoe state must be running in order to start the DUT!

Channel 08 is an output that is used to drive an LED labelled 'PWM dimmable LED'.
It is also displayed on the CANoe.</Property>
    </Object>
